value.title: Kamala Harris pays tribute to RBG with Supreme Court pic
value.excerpt: Democratic Vice Presidential candidate Kamala Harris paid tribute to the passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsberg Saturday, calling the liberal icon a “titan.”

value.title: Ginsburg vacancy puts pressure on Trump-critic Republicans in Senate
value.excerpt: Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg’s death Friday has put a spotlight on a handful of unpredictable Republican senators.

value.title: Trump on whether FBI Director Wray could be replaced: 'We're looking at a lot of different things'
value.excerpt: The president ripped Wray for his comments regarding Russian election interference and Antifa.

value.title: Kosovo gives Trump Order of Freedom for his role in securing deal with Serbia
value.excerpt: Kosovo gave President Trump one of its highest honors on Friday for his role in an historic economic normalization deal with Serbia earlier this month.

value.title: Trump vows enough coronavirus vaccine doses for ‘every American’ by April
value.excerpt: President Trump, during a White House press conference on Friday, said the United States will produce enough coronavirus vaccine doses for “every American” by April.

value.title: What’s up with Trump and the Hispanic vote?
value.excerpt: Voters may have noticed what’s missing from Trump’s reelection pitch compared to his campaign of four years ago: Immigration.

value.title: Ivanka Trump raises $7.5 million for campaign in Texas, Florida trips
value.excerpt: White House adviser Ivanka Trump raised $7.5 million for her father’s campaign in trips to Texas and Florida over the past week, a Trump aide familiar with fundraising told Fox News.

value.title: Joe Biden, CNN’s Anderson Cooper appear to dispense with social distancing during town hall commercial break
value.excerpt: A former CNN employee noticed that Anderson Cooper and Joe Biden stopped social distancing during Thursday’s town hall when they thought the liberal network cut to a commercial.

value.title: 'O.C.' actress Samaire Armstrong voices support for Trump, says 'far left mob' has silenced Americans
value.excerpt: The O.C.” actress Samaire Armstrong posted a passionate video on Wednesday pledging her support for Donald Trump for the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Biden changes answer on national mask mandate authority again, says he would not have power to enforce it
value.excerpt: Biden has vacillated back and forth on whether he could or would enforce a national mask mandate as president

value.title: Trump supporters in battleground Wisconsin reveal what issues matter most nearing election
value.excerpt: Investigative Reporter Lawrence Jones spoke with Wisconsin voters about why they're voting for President Trump and what concerns them most.

value.title: Biden blasts AG Barr for comments comparing coronavirus restrictions to slavery
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden went after Attorney General Bill Barr during a CNN Town Hall Thursday evening, calling Barr’s linking of coronavirus restrictions to slavery, “outrageous.”

value.title: Victor Davis Hanson argues Biden is being ‘held hostage’ by his own party
value.excerpt: Hoover Institution Senior Fellow Victor Davis Hanson said Joe Biden is being held hostage by the Democrats as to not compromise his own campaign.

value.title: Netflix star under FBI investigation for soliciting sex from minors previously held Instagram session with Biden
value.excerpt: A popular Netflix personality who is reportedly under FBI investigation for soliciting nude photos from minors helped boost Joe Biden's presidential campaign earlier this year.

value.title: Trump HHS spokesperson Michael Caputo deletes Twitter account after late-night rant
value.excerpt: The top spokesperson for the Department of Health and Human Services deleted his Twitter in the aftermath of a late-night rant in which he suggested tear gassing journalists and battled with other users on the social media platform.

value.title: Lt. Col. Vindman says he now identifies as a 'Never Trumper'
value.excerpt: Lt. Col. Alexander Vindman says he now identifies as a "Never Trumper" following his official retirement from the military.

value.title: Trump awards Distinguished Flying Cross to 7 California National Guard members
value.excerpt: President Trump on Monday awarded the Distinguished Flying Cross to seven members of the California National Guard who helped rescue over 200 people earlier this month from the massive wildfire.

value.title: Trump campaign returns to economy with 8-figure ad buy, calls it ‘defining issue in this race’
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign is set to release a mid-eight-figure ad buy Tuesday touting the economy during President Trump's first term after a recent emphasis on "law and order" messaging, saying the economy is the "defining issue" of the 2020 presidential race, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Biden argues he's in better shape than Trump: 'Just look at us'
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden went on the offensive on Sunday in the war of words between him and President Trump over who the fittest man – both mentally and physically – to lead the country.

value.title: Trump slams Bill de Blasio for telling New Yorkers to enjoy ‘beautiful’ day in NYC
value.excerpt: President Trump mocked New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio on Twitter Sunday for telling city residents to enjoy the day amid heightened crime.

value.title: Trump signs executive order to lower drug prices in fight against Big Pharma
value.excerpt: The new order follows a series of four orders President Trump signed in July that similarly lowered prices of prescription drugs.

value.title: Bloomberg to back Biden by spending $100M in Florida
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden's onetime rival, billionaire Mike Bloomberg, will spend $100 million to get Biden elected in Florida.

value.title: Joe Biden And Mike Pence Exchange Elbow Bump At NYC 9/11 Memorial Event
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and former Vice President Joe Biden greeted each other at the annual ceremony commemorating 9/11 in New York, a calm respite from a bitter 2020 election campaign.
